\f0\b \cf2 Property Fitting\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0 \cf2 \
Property fitting is a method of analyzing the proximities based on dimension to get an idea of which attributes may have affected the coordinates of each city. In our case it makes it possible to plot the attributes and preferences into the cartesian space that resulted from the MDS. \
\
First it is necessary relate the position in the cartesian space to the individual properties. A linear regression with the attributes as the dependent variables, and the coordinates of the cities as the independent variables is being used to achieve this goal. The regression summary for the attribute \'84romantic\'93 is displayed below.\
