The results of the property fitting are in line with what one might expect. Paris and Rome are related to the attributes \'84romantic\'93 and \'84historical\'93. London and Dublin are outstandingly \'84english speaker friendly\'93. Stockholm, Brussels and Geneva score high on being \'84clean\'93 and \'84safe\'93. Berlin, Amsterdam and London are both \'84fun\'93, \'84trendy\'93 and \'84international\'93, but also \'84too touristic\'93. \
\
Lastly the cities in the second quadrant appear to be particularly correlated with the preferences for a good city trip of the queried respondents. \
